Karst Underwater Research is a registered 501(c)(3) non-profit organization that specializes in the professional documentation and research of Karst aquifers and their corresponding surface features with over 20 years of experience. Utilizing trained and experienced individuals, KUR performs a variety of scientific processes: mapping and cartography, radio location, photography, videography, YSI water analysis and sampling.
Karst Underwater Research Mission Statement: To protect and provide continued preservation of Karst aquifers and the quality of their water by conducting relevant scientific research and documentation of surface features and corresponding underwater caverns and conduits.


